author: Tomeyjes For Metro.Co.Uk
title: Flight from Edinburgh crash lands off runway during Storm Doris | Metro News
text:
Toby Meyjes for Metro.co.uk Thursday 23 Feb 2017 4:48 pm The plane’s landing gear failed during its landing (Picture: David Fleming Jr) 
A plane has crashed off the runway at Amsterdam’s Schiphol Airport during high winds. 
The FlyBe flight from Edinburgh was pictured with collapsed landing gear. 
All passengers are said to have been brought to the terminal by bus and no one was injured. 
The airport confirmed the incident on Twitter saying the plane’s landing gear collapsed during touch down. 
It later added that flights were once again fully operational. The landing gear of a FLybe airplane collapsed during touch down. All passengers are brought to the terminal by bus at the moment.
